{"_id":"0fcc160c24bacfe5","name":"FLTCH-Series_Battle_Droid","type":"droid","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"degree":"4th-Degree","initiative":null,"senses":"Perception","perception":11,"reflexDefense":19,"flatFooted":17,"fortitudeDefense":22,"willDefense":14,"HP":32,"damageThreshold":22,"speed":8,"baseAttackBonus":null,"grapple":null,"attacks":{"melee":[{"name":"Unarmed","bonus":13,"damage":"1d6+8"}],"ranged":[{"name":"Heavy Blaster Rifle","bonus":10,"damage":"3d10+2"},{"name":"Blaster Rifle","bonus":10,"damage":"3d8+2"},{"name":"Missile Launcher","bonus":9,"damage":"6d6, 2-Square Burst"}]},"baseStats":{"abilities":{"strength":22,"dexterity":15,"intelligence":12,"wisdom":11,"charisma":8,"constitution":0}},"skills":{"Endurance":9,"Perception":11,"Persuasion":8},"type":"droid","description":"","costNumeric":31375,"category":"droid","cost":31375,"droidDegreeKey":"4th-degree","droidRole":"battle","droidRoleLabel":"Battle","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Basic Processor , 2 Claw Appendages, Improved Sensor Package , Vocabulator","droidSystems":{"processor":{"id":"basic-processor","name":"Basic Processor","source":"published"},"locomotion":[{"id":"walking-locomotion","name":"Walking Locomotion","source":"published"}],"appendages":[{"id":"2-claw-appendages","name":"2 Claw Appendages","source":"published"}],"sensors":[{"id":"improved-sensor-package","name":"Improved Sensor Package","source":"published"}],"integratedSystems":[{"id":"vocabulator","name":"Vocabulator","source":"published"}],"accessories":[],"weapons":[{"id":"heavy-blaster-rifle","name":"Heavy Blaster Rifle","mode":"ranged","damage":"3d10+2","attackBonus":10,"source":"published-attack"},{"id":"blaster-rifle","name":"Blaster Rifle","mode":"ranged","damage":"3d8+2","attackBonus":10,"source":"published-attack"},{"id":"missile-launcher","name":"Missile Launcher","mode":"ranged","damage":"6d6, 2-Square Burst","attackBonus":9,"source":"published-attack"}],"sourceText":"Walking Locomotion, Basic Processor , 2 Claw Appendages, Improved Sensor Package , Vocabulator","sourcePossessions":"Blaster Rifle , Heavy Blaster Rifle , Missile Launcher (1 Missile), Jet Pack , Quadanium Battle Armor ( Droid Armor ; +7 Reflex ) Availability: Military ; Cost: 31,375 credits Abilities [ ] Nightmare: The FLTCH-Series Battle Droid uses its claws and spikes to intimidate while attacking. Once per encounter, the Droid can make a Persuasion check to Intimidate an enemy as a Free Action while it simultaneously makes a melee attack against the same enemy. If the check is successful, the intimidation takes effect after the Droid's turn is complete. Zero-Range Attack: If the FLTCH-Series Battle Droid makes a successful attempt to Grab or Grapple an enemy with its Claw Appendage, it can make an immediate attack with its arm-mounted Blaster Rifle . FLTCH-Series Battle Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Large 4th-Degree Droid Hit Points: 32 Damage Threshold : 22 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The FLTCH-Series Battle Droid moves 8 squares ( Walking ) or 6 squares ( Jet Pack ). Claw Attack (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The FLTCH-Series Battle Droid makes a melee attack at +13. If successful, the attack deals 1d6+8 points of damage. Heavy Blaster Rifle Attack (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The FLTCH-Series Battle Droid makes a ranged attack at +10. If successful, the attack deals 3d10+2 points of damage. Missile Launcher Attack (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The FLTCH-Series Battle Droid makes a ranged attack at +9. If successful, the attack deals 6d6+2 points of damage in a 2-square radius. Nightmare (2 Swift Actions , 1/Encounter) [ ] The FLTCH-Series Battle Droid makes a Persuasion check to Intimidate an enemy while it simultaneously makes a melee attack against the same enemy. If the check is successful, the intimidation takes effect after the Droid's turn is complete. Zero-Range Attack (2 Swift Actions , 1/Encounter) [ ] The FLTCH-Series Battle Droid attempts to Grab or Grapple an enemy with its Claw Appendage at +13. If the attack is successful, the Droid can make an immediate attack at +10 with its arm-mounted Blaster Rifle , dealing 3d8+2 points of damage. Base Stats [ ]"},"cl":5},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"speedText":"8 Squares ( Walking ), 6 Squares ( Jet Pack ); Running Attack","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Basic Processor , 2 Claw Appendages, Improved Sensor Package , Vocabulator"}}}
