{"_id":"69a2e074d7442dbd","name":"F1_Exploration_Droid","type":"droid","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"degree":"5th-Degree","initiative":7,"senses":"Perception","perception":15,"reflexDefense":17,"flatFooted":16,"fortitudeDefense":15,"willDefense":15,"HP":33,"damageThreshold":15,"speed":4,"baseAttackBonus":null,"grapple":null,"attacks":{"melee":[{"name":"Bite","bonus":3,"damage":"1d3+2"},{"name":"Bite","bonus":3,"damage":"1d3+2"}],"ranged":[]},"baseStats":{"abilities":{"strength":13,"dexterity":13,"intelligence":8,"wisdom":14,"charisma":10,"constitution":0}},"skills":{"Initiative":7,"Jump":7,"Perception":15,"Stealth":17,"Survival":8},"type":"droid","description":"","costNumeric":12500,"category":"droid","cost":12500,"droidDegreeKey":"5th-degree","droidRole":"exploration","droidRoleLabel":"Exploration","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Extra Legs , Basic Processor , 1 Claw Appendage (Bite), Darkvision , Improved Sensor Package , Internal Comlink Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 12,500 credits Abilities [ ] Motion Sensors: The motion sensor suite installed in the F1 Exploration Droid allows it to reroll its Perception check and keep the better of the two results. In addition, this carries over to its master's Perception check when trying to locate the same target, allowing the master to reroll his or her Perception check and keep the better result. F1 Exploration Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Small 5th-Degree Droid Hit Points: 33 Damage Threshold : 15 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The F1 Exploration Droid moves 4 squares ( Walking ). Create a Diversion to Hide (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The F1 Exploration Droid can make a Deception check (+0) to Create a Diversion to Hide and giving its master time to hide. Motion Sensors (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] When its master uses the Notice Targets application of the Perception skill, the F1 Exploration Droid enables its master to reroll the Perception check, keeping the better result. Search (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] Using its improved sensors, the F1 Exploration Droid can help locate a specific person or object by granting a +2 bonus to its master's Perception check. Track (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The F1 Exploration Droid can Track with a successful Survival check. Base Stats [ ] Skills : Initiative +7, Jump +7, Perception +15 (may reroll, may keep better result), Stealth +17 (may reroll, must take second result), Survival +8 Vital Systems: 1 Claw Appendage (Bite), Internal Comlink","droidSystems":{"processor":{"id":"basic-processor","name":"Basic Processor","source":"published"},"locomotion":[{"id":"walking-locomotion","name":"Walking Locomotion","source":"published"},{"id":"allowing-the-master-to-reroll-his-or-her-perception-check-and-keep-the-better-result-f1-exploration-droid-protocol-format-see-also-protocol-format-small-5th-degree-droid-hit-points-33-damage-threshold-15-system-actions-move-1-swift-action-2-turn-the-f1-exploration-droid-moves-4-squares-walking-create-a-diversion-to-hide-1-swift-action-1-turn-the-f1-exploration-droid-can-make-a-deception-check-0-to-create-a-diversion-to-hide-and-giving-its-master-time-to-hide-motion-sensors-2-swift-actions-1-turn-when-its-master-uses-the-notice-targets-application-of-the-perception-skill","name":"allowing the master to reroll his or her Perception check and keep the better result. F1 Exploration Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Small 5th-Degree Droid Hit Points: 33 Damage Threshold : 15 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action, 2/Turn) [ ] The F1 Exploration Droid moves 4 squares ( Walking ). Create a Diversion to Hide (1 Swift Action, 1/Turn) [ ] The F1 Exploration Droid can make a Deception check (+0) to Create a Diversion to Hide and giving its master time to hide. Motion Sensors (2 Swift Actions, 1/Turn) [ ] When its master uses the Notice Targets application of the Perception skill","source":"published"}],"appendages":[{"id":"1-claw-appendage-bite","name":"1 Claw Appendage (Bite)","source":"published"},{"id":"survival-8-vital-systems-1-claw-appendage-bite","name":"Survival +8 Vital Systems: 1 Claw Appendage (Bite)","source":"published"}],"sensors":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","source":"published"},{"id":"improved-sensor-package","name":"Improved Sensor Package","source":"published"},{"id":"500-credits-abilities-motion-sensors-the-motion-sensor-suite-installed-in-the-f1-exploration-droid-allows-it-to-reroll-its-perception-check-and-keep-the-better-of-the-two-results-in-addition","name":"500 credits Abilities [ ] Motion Sensors: The motion sensor suite installed in the F1 Exploration Droid allows it to reroll its Perception check and keep the better of the two results. In addition","source":"published"},{"id":"keeping-the-better-result-search-1-swift-action-1-turn-using-its-improved-sensors","name":"keeping the better result. Search (1 Swift Action, 1/Turn) [ ] Using its improved sensors","source":"published"}],"integratedSystems":[{"id":"internal-comlink-availability-licensed-cost-12","name":"Internal Comlink Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 12","source":"published"},{"id":"internal-comlink","name":"Internal Comlink","source":"published"}],"accessories":[{"id":"extra-legs","name":"Extra Legs","source":"published"},{"id":"this-carries-over-to-its-masters-perception-check-when-trying-to-locate-the-same-target","name":"this carries over to its master's Perception check when trying to locate the same target","source":"published"},{"id":"the-f1-exploration-droid-enables-its-master-to-reroll-the-perception-check","name":"the F1 Exploration Droid enables its master to reroll the Perception check","source":"published"},{"id":"the-f1-exploration-droid-can-help-locate-a-specific-person-or-object-by-granting-a-2-bonus-to-its-masters-perception-check-track-2-swift-actions-1-turn-the-f1-exploration-droid-can-track-with-a-successful-survival-check-base-stats-skills-initiative-7","name":"the F1 Exploration Droid can help locate a specific person or object by granting a +2 bonus to its master's Perception check. Track (2 Swift Actions, 1/Turn) [ ] The F1 Exploration Droid can Track with a successful Survival check. Base Stats [ ] Skills : Initiative +7","source":"published"},{"id":"jump-7","name":"Jump +7","source":"published"},{"id":"perception-15-may-reroll-may-keep-better-result","name":"Perception +15 (may reroll, may keep better result)","source":"published"},{"id":"stealth-17-may-reroll-must-take-second-result","name":"Stealth +17 (may reroll, must take second result)","source":"published"}],"weapons":[{"id":"bite","name":"Bite","mode":"melee","damage":"1d3+2","attackBonus":3,"source":"published-attack"},{"id":"bite","name":"Bite","mode":"melee","damage":"1d3+2","attackBonus":3,"source":"published-attack"}],"sourceText":"Walking Locomotion, Extra Legs , Basic Processor , 1 Claw Appendage (Bite), Darkvision , Improved Sensor Package , Internal Comlink Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 12,500 credits Abilities [ ] Motion Sensors: The motion sensor suite installed in the F1 Exploration Droid allows it to reroll its Perception check and keep the better of the two results. In addition, this carries over to its master's Perception check when trying to locate the same target, allowing the master to reroll his or her Perception check and keep the better result. F1 Exploration Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Small 5th-Degree Droid Hit Points: 33 Damage Threshold : 15 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The F1 Exploration Droid moves 4 squares ( Walking ). Create a Diversion to Hide (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The F1 Exploration Droid can make a Deception check (+0) to Create a Diversion to Hide and giving its master time to hide. Motion Sensors (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] When its master uses the Notice Targets application of the Perception skill, the F1 Exploration Droid enables its master to reroll the Perception check, keep