erson or object by granting a +2 bonus to its master's Perception check. Track (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The F1 Exploration Droid can Track with a successful Survival check. Base Stats [ ] Skills : Initiative +7, Jump +7, Perception +15 (may reroll, may keep better result), Stealth +17 (may reroll, must take second result), Survival +8 Vital Systems: 1 Claw Appendage (Bite), Internal Comlink"}}}
{"_id":"6be667ae63e303ee","name":"A-Series_Medical_Droid","type":"droid","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"degree":"1st-Degree","initiative":5,"senses":"Perception","perception":7,"reflexDefense":13,"flatFooted":13,"fortitudeDefense":10,"willDefense":15,"HP":18,"damageThreshold":10,"speed":4,"baseAttackBonus":null,"grapple":null,"attacks":{"melee":[{"name":"Unarmed","bonus":-1,"damage":"1d2-1"}],"ranged":[]},"baseStats":{"abilities":{"strength":8,"dexterity":10,"intelligence":14,"wisdom":15,"charisma":12,"constitution":0}},"skills":{"Initiative":5,"Perception":7,"Persuasion":6,"Treat Injury":12,"Use Computer":7},"type":"droid","description":"","costNumeric":9740,"category":"droid","cost":9740,"droidDegreeKey":"1st-degree","droidRole":"medical","droidRoleLabel":"Medical","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Heuristic Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, 3 Tool Mounts, Diagnostics Package , Vocabulator","droidSystems":{"processor":{"id":"heuristic-processor","name":"Heuristic Processor","source":"published"},"locomotion":[{"id":"walking-locomotion","name":"Walking Locomotion","source":"published"}],"appendages":[{"id":"2-hand-appendages","name":"2 Hand Appendages","source":"published"},{"id":"3-tool-mounts","name":"3 Tool Mounts","source":"published"}],"sensors":[],"integratedSystems":[{"id":"vocabulator","name":"Vocabulator","source":"published"}],"accessories":[{"id":"diagnostics-package","name":"Diagnostics Package","source":"published"}],"weapons":[],"sourceText":"Walking Locomotion, Heuristic Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, 3 Tool Mounts, Diagnostics Package , Vocabulator","sourcePossessions":"Medical Kit , Medpac (5), Surgery Kit Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 9,740 credits * Reprogrammed"},"cl":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"speedText":"4 Squares ( Walking )","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Heuristic Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, 3 Tool Mounts, Diagnostics Package , Vocabulator"}}}
{"_id":"6f2487c5d9fac65a","name":"LEP_Service_Droid","type":"droid","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"degree":"3rd-Degree","initiative":null,"senses":"Perception","perception":10,"reflexDefense":11,"flatFooted":11,"fortitudeDefense":8,"willDefense":10,"HP":3,"damageThreshold":8,"speed":4,"baseAttackBonus":null,"grapple":null,"attacks":{"melee":[{"name":"Unarmed","bonus":-2,"damage":"1d2-2"}],"ranged":[]},"baseStats":{"abilities":{"strength":7,"dexterity":11,"intelligence":12,"wisdom":10,"charisma":14,"constitution":0}},"skills":{"Perception":10,"Persuasion":12,"Treat Injury":10,"Use Computer":6},"type":"droid","description":"","costNumeric":6260,"category":"droid","cost":6260,"droidDegreeKey":"3rd-degree","droidRole":"service","droidRoleLabel":"Service","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Basic Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, 2 Probe Appendages, Compartment Space (30 kg), Vocabulator Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 6,260 credits Abilities [ ] Empathic: Although the LEP Service Droid is not literally empathic, its keen sense of awareness allows it to pick up on the subtle mannerisms and emotional expressions of its master and other organic creatures and appeal to their emotions. The Droid can reroll its Persuasion check to Change Attitude of its intended target, and can take the better of the two results. LEP Service Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Small 3rd-Degree Droid Hit Points: 3 Damage Threshold : 8 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid moves 4 squares ( Walking ). Empathic (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid can improve the Attitude of its target by rerolling a Persuasion check and taking the better of the two results. First Aid (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes a DC 15 Treat Injury check on a target in an adjacent square. If the check is successful, the target regains a number of Hit Points equal to its Character Level +1 for every point by which the check was successful. A character can be treated with First Aid in this manner only once per day. Haggle (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes a Persuasion check to help its master negotiate a better deal. If the check is successful, the Droid grants its master a +2 bonus to his or her Persuasion check. Revivify (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes a DC 20 Treat Injury check on a target currently at 0 Hit Points in an adjacent square. If the check is successful, the target is Unconscious instead of Dead . Treat Poison ( 2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn ) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes Treat Injury check to cure a character suffering from Poison , with a DC equal to the Poison's Challenge Level. Base Stats [ ] Skills : Perception +10, Persuasion +12 (may reroll to Change Attitude , may keep better result), Treat Injury +10, Use Computer +6 Vital Systems: 2 Hand Appendages, 2 Probe Appendages, Vocabulator","droidSystems":{"processor":{"id":"basic-processor","name":"Basic Processor","source":"published"},"locomotion":[{"id":"walking-locomotion","name":"Walking Locomotion","source":"published"},{"id":"and-can-take-the-better-of-the-two-results-lep-service-droid-protocol-format-see-also-protocol-format-small-3rd-degree-droid-hit-points-3-damage-threshold-8-system-actions-move-1-swift-action-2-turn-the-lep-service-droid-moves-4-squares-walking-empathic-2-swift-actions-1-turn-the-lep-service-droid-can-improve-the-attitude-of-its-target-by-rerolling-a-persuasion-check-and-taking-the-better-of-the-two-results-first-aid-2-swift-actions-1-turn-the-lep-service-droid-makes-a-dc-15-treat-injury-check-on-a-target-in-an-adjacent-square-if-the-check-is-successful","name":"and can take the better of the two results. LEP Service Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Small 3rd-Degree Droid Hit Points: 3 Damage Threshold : 8 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action, 2/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid moves 4 squares ( Walking ). Empathic (2 Swift Actions, 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid can improve the Attitude of its target by rerolling a Persuasion check and taking the better of the two results. First Aid (2 Swift Actions, 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes a DC 15 Treat Injury check on a target in an adjacent square. If the check is successful","source":"published"}],"appendages":[{"id":"2-hand-appendages","name":"2 Hand Appendages","source":"published"},{"id":"2-probe-appendages","name":"2 Probe Appendages","source":"published"},{"id":"use-computer-6-vital-systems-2-hand-appendages","name":"Use Computer +6 Vital Systems: 2 Hand Appendages","source":"published"},{"id":"2-probe-appendages","name":"2 Probe Appendages","source":"published"}],"sensors":[],"integratedSystems":[{"id":"vocabulator-availability-licensed-cost-6","name":"Vocabulator Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 6","source":"published"},{"id":"vocabulator","name":"Vocabulator","source":"published"}],"accessories":[{"id":"compartment-space-30-kg","name":"Compartment Space (30 kg)","source":"published"},{"id":"260-credits-abilities-empathic-although-the-lep-service-droid-is-not-literally-empathic","name":"260 credits Abilities [ ] Empathic: Although the LEP Service Droid is not literally empathic","source":"published"},{"id":"its-keen-sense-of-awareness-allows-it-to-pick-up-on-the-subtle-mannerisms-and-emotional-expressions-of-its-master-and-other-organic-creatures-and-appeal-to-their-emotions-the-droid-can-reroll-its-persuasion-check-to-change-attitude-of-its-intended-target","name":"its keen sense of awareness allows it to pick up on the subtle mannerisms and emotional expressions of its master and other organic creatures and appeal to their emotions. The Droid can reroll its Persuasion check to Change Attitude of its intended target","source":"published"},{"id":"the-target-regains-a-number-of-hit-points-equal-to-its-character-level-1-for-every-point-by-which-the-check-was-successful-a-character-can-be-treated-with-first-aid-in-this-manner-only-once-per-day-haggle-1-swift-action-1-turn-the-lep-service-droid-makes-a-persuasion-check-to-help-its-master-negotiate-a-better-deal-if-the-check-is-successful","name":"the target regains a number of Hit Points equal to its Character Level +1 for every point by which the check was successful. A character can be treated with First Aid in this manner only once per day. Haggle (1 Swift Action, 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes a Persuasion check to help its master negotiate a better deal. If the check is successful","source":"published"},{"id":"the-droid-grants-its-master-a-2-bonus-to-his-or-her-persuasion-check-revivify-2-swift-actions-1-turn-the-lep-service-droid-makes-a-dc-20-treat-injury-check-on-a-target-currently-at-0-hit-points-in-an-adjacent-square-if-the-check-is-successful","name":"the Droid grants its master a +2 bonus to his or her Persuasion check. Revivify (2 Swift Actions, 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes a DC 20 Treat Injury check on a target currently at 0 Hit Points in an adjacent square. If the check is successful","source":"published"},{"id":"the-target-is-unconscious-instead-of-dead-treat-poison-2-swift-actions-1-turn-the-lep-service-droid-makes-treat-injury-check-to-cure-a-character-suffering-from-poison","name":"the target is Unconscious instead of Dead . Treat Poison ( 2 Swift Actions, 1/Turn ) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes Treat Injury check to cure a character suffering from Poison","source":"published"},{"id":"with-a-dc-equal-to-the-poisons-challenge-level-base-stats-skills-perception-10","name":"with a DC equal to the Poison's Challenge Level. Base Stats [ ] Skills : Perception +10","source":"published"},{"id":"persuasion-12-may-reroll-to-change-attitude-may-keep-better-result","name":"Persuasion +12 (may reroll to Change Attitude, may keep better result)","source":"published"},{"id":"treat-injury-10","name":"Treat Injury +10","source":"published"}],"weapons":[],"sourceText":"Walking Locomotion, Basic Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, 2 Probe Appendages, Compartment Space (30 kg), Vocabulator Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 6,260 credits Abilities [ ] Empathic: Although the LEP Service Droid is not literally empathic, its keen sense of awareness allows it to pick up on the subtle mannerisms and emotional expressions of its master and other organic creatures and appeal to their emotions. The Droid can reroll its Persuasion check to Change Attitude of its intended target, and can take the better of the two results. LEP Service Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Small 3rd-Degree Droid Hit Points: 3 Damage Threshold : 8 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid moves 4 squares ( Walking ). Empathic (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid can improve the Attitude of its target by rerolling a Persuasion check and taking the better of the two results. First Aid (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes a DC 15 Treat Injury check on a target in an adjacent square. If the check is successful, the target regains a number of Hit Points equal to its Character Level +1 for every point by which the check was successful. A character can be treated with First Aid in this manner only once per day. Haggle (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes a Persuasion check to help its master negotiate a better deal. If the check is successful, the Droid grants its master a +2 bonus to his or her Persuasion check. Revivify (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes a DC 20 Treat Injury check on a target currently at 0 Hit Points in an adjacent square. If the check is successful, the target is Unconscious instead of Dead . Treat Poison ( 2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn ) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes Treat Injury check to cure a character suffering from Poison , with a DC equal to the Poison's Challenge Level. Base Stats [ ] Skills : Perception +10, Persuasion +12 (may reroll to Change Attitude , may keep better result), Treat Injury +10, Use Computer +6 Vital Systems: 2 Hand Appendages, 2 Probe Appendages, Vocabulator"},"cl":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"speedText":"4 Squares ( Walking )","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Basic Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, 2 Probe Appendages, Compartment Space (30 kg), Vocabulator Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 6,260 credits Abilities [ ] Empathic: Although the LEP Service Droid is not literally empathic, its keen sense of awareness allows it to pick up on the subtle mannerisms and emotional expressions of its master and other organic creatures and appeal to their emotions. The Droid can reroll its Persuasion check to Change Attitude of its intended target, and can take the better of the two results. LEP Service Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Small 3rd-Degree Droid Hit Points: 3 Damage Threshold : 8 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid moves 4 squares ( Walking ). Empathic (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid can improve the Attitude of its target by rerolling a Persuasion check and taking the better of the two results. First Aid (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes a DC 15 Treat Injury check on a target in an adjacent square. If the check is successful, the target regains a number of Hit Points equal to its Character Level +1 for every point by which the check was successful. A character can be treated with First Aid in this manner only once per day. Haggle (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes a Persuasion check to help its master negotiate a better deal. If the check is successful, the Droid grants its master a +2 bonus to his or her Persuasion check. Revivify (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes a DC 20 Treat Injury check on a target currently at 0 Hit Points in an adjacent square. If the check is successful, the target is Unconscious instead of Dead . Treat Poison ( 2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn ) [ ] The LEP Service Droid makes Treat Injury check to cure a character suffering from Poison , with a DC equal to the Poison's Challenge Level. Base Stats [ ] Skills : Perception +10, Persuasion +12 (may reroll to Change Attitude , may keep better result), Treat Injury +10, Use Computer +6 Vital Systems: 2 Hand Appendages, 2 Probe Appendages, Vocabulator"}}}
