{"_id":"8174aef071163519","name":"88-Series_Administration_Droid","type":"droid","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"degree":"1st-Degree","initiative":null,"senses":"Perception","perception":11,"reflexDefense":13,"flatFooted":13,"fortitudeDefense":12,"willDefense":17,"HP":26,"damageThreshold":12,"speed":6,"baseAttackBonus":null,"grapple":null,"attacks":{"melee":[{"name":"Unarmed","bonus":5,"damage":"1d3"}],"ranged":[]},"baseStats":{"abilities":{"strength":8,"dexterity":8,"intelligence":16,"wisdom":14,"charisma":12,"constitution":0}},"skills":{"Deception":10,"Gather Information":15,"Perception":11,"Persuasion":10,"Stealth":8,"Use Computer":12},"type":"droid","description":"","costNumeric":15000,"category":"droid","cost":15000,"droidDegreeKey":"1st-degree","droidRole":"analysis","droidRoleLabel":"Analysis","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Heuristic Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, Internal Comlink , Internal Storage (5 kg), Vocabulator","droidSystems":{"processor":{"id":"heuristic-processor","name":"Heuristic Processor","source":"published"},"locomotion":[{"id":"walking-locomotion","name":"Walking Locomotion","source":"published"}],"appendages":[{"id":"2-hand-appendages","name":"2 Hand Appendages","source":"published"}],"sensors":[],"integratedSystems":[{"id":"internal-comlink","name":"Internal Comlink","source":"published"},{"id":"vocabulator","name":"Vocabulator","source":"published"}],"accessories":[{"id":"internal-storage-5-kg","name":"Internal Storage (5 kg)","source":"published"}],"weapons":[],"sourceText":"Walking Locomotion, Heuristic Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, Internal Comlink , Internal Storage (5 kg), Vocabulator","sourcePossessions":"Datapad Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 15,000 credits Abilities [ ] Superior Analysis: When an 88-Series Administration Droid fails any Knowledge check, it can immediately make a Perception check, add half the total to the previous Knowledge check, and take the new result. Timely Observation: Once per encounter, an 88-Series Administration Droid can make a DC 20 Perception check as a Free Action on its turn. If the check is successful, the Droid observes a physical or psychological weakness in an opponent. The Droid gains a + 1 bonus to its next attack roll or opposed skill check against that opponent. Alternatively, the Droid can grant the bonus to an ally who can see or hear the Droid for use on the ally's next turn. 88-Series Administration Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Medium 1st-Degree Droid Hit Points: 26 Damage Threshold : 12 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The 88-Series Administration Droid moves 6 squares ( Walking ). Improve Access (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The 88-Series Administration Droid makes a Use Computer check against the target computer's Will Defense to improve the computer's Attitude toward it. Issue Routine Command (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The 88-Series Administration Droid issues a routine command to a computer that has a Friendly Attitude toward it. Superior Analysis ( Reaction ) [ ] When an 88-Series Administration Droid fails any Knowledge check, it can immediately make a Perception check, add half the total to the previous Knowledge check, and take the new result. Timely Observation (1 Free Action , 1/Encounter) [ ] An 88-Series Administration Droid can make a DC 20 Perception check on its turn. If the check is successful, the Droid observes a physical or psychological weakness in an opponent. The Droid gains a + 1 bonus to its next attack roll or opposed skill check against that opponent. Alternatively, the Droid can grant the bonus to an ally who can see or hear the Droid for use on the ally's next turn. Base Stats [ ]"},"cl":5},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"speedText":"6 Squares ( Walking )","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Heuristic Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, Internal Comlink , Internal Storage (5 kg), Vocabulator"}}}
{"_id":"820b79bc8916569e","name":"A9G-Series_Archive_Droid","type":"droid","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"degree":"1st-Degree","initiative":null,"senses":"Perception","perception":1,"reflexDefense":10,"flatFooted":10,"fortitudeDefense":10,"willDefense":10,"HP":7,"damageThreshold":10,"speed":6,"baseAttackBonus":null,"grapple":null,"attacks":{"melee":[{"name":"Unarmed","bonus":1,"damage":"1d3"}],"ranged":[]},"baseStats":{"abilities":{"strength":10,"dexterity":11,"intelligence":14,"wisdom":10,"charisma":12,"constitution":0}},"skills":{"Gather Information":12,"Perception":1,"Use Computer":13},"type":"droid","description":"","costNumeric":6880,"category":"droid","cost":6880,"droidDegreeKey":"1st-degree","droidRole":"analysis","droidRoleLabel":"Analysis","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Heuristic Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, Translator Unit (DC 10), Vocabulator","droidSystems":{"processor":{"id":"heuristic-processor","name":"Heuristic Processor","source":"published"},"locomotion":[{"id":"walking-locomotion","name":"Walking Locomotion","source":"published"}],"appendages":[{"id":"2-hand-appendages","name":"2 Hand Appendages","source":"published"}],"sensors":[],"integratedSystems":[{"id":"translator-unit-dc-10","name":"Translator Unit (DC 10)","source":"published"},{"id":"vocabulator","name":"Vocabulator","source":"published"}],"accessories":[],"weapons":[],"sourceText":"Walking Locomotion, Heuristic Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, Translator Unit (DC 10), Vocabulator","sourcePossessions":"Code Cylinder , Storage Device (20 Memory Units) Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 6,880 credits Abilities [ ] Archive Processor: As a Full-Round Action , the A9G-Series Archive Droid can quickly sift through volumes of information stored in a computer network while searching for a specific piece of data. The Droid can reroll Gather Information or Knowledge checks when attempting to retrieve information from a computer system, but must keep the second result, even if it is worse. A9G-Series Archive Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Medium 1st-Degree Droid Hit Points: 7 Damage Threshold : 10 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The A9G-Series Archive Droid moves 6 squares ( Walking ). Archive Processor (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The A9G-Series Archive Droid can reroll Gather Information or Knowledge checks while connected to a computer system, but must keep the second result, even if it is worse. Improve Access (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The A9G-Series Archive Droid makes a Use Computer check against the target computer's Will Defense to improve the computer's Attitude toward it. Issue Routine Command (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The A9G-Series Archive Droid issues a routine command to a computer that has a Friendly Attitude toward it. Translator (1 Free Action ) [ ] With a DC 10 Intelligence check, the A9G-Series Archive Droid translates to or from any language it knows. Base Stats [ ]"},"cl":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"speedText":"6 Squares ( Walking )","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Heuristic Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, Translator Unit (DC 10), Vocabulator"}}}
