{"_id":"9d4c0dc59699a9e6","name":"XLT-014_Labor_Droid","type":"droid","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"degree":"5th-Degree","initiative":null,"senses":"Perception","perception":12,"reflexDefense":14,"flatFooted":14,"fortitudeDefense":12,"willDefense":12,"HP":4,"damageThreshold":12,"speed":6,"baseAttackBonus":null,"grapple":null,"attacks":{"melee":[{"name":"Unarmed","bonus":2,"damage":"1d4+2"}],"ranged":[]},"baseStats":{"abilities":{"strength":14,"dexterity":10,"intelligence":8,"wisdom":14,"charisma":10,"constitution":0}},"skills":{"Perception":12,"Use Computer":9},"type":"droid","description":"","costNumeric":9600,"category":"droid","cost":9600,"droidDegreeKey":"5th-degree","droidRole":"labor","droidRoleLabel":"Labor","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Hovering Locomotion ( Limited ), Remote Receiver , 2 Claw Appendages, Vocabulator","droidSystems":{"processor":{"id":"remote-receiver","name":"Remote Receiver","source":"published"},"locomotion":[{"id":"walking-locomotion","name":"Walking Locomotion","source":"published"},{"id":"hovering-locomotion-limited","name":"Hovering Locomotion ( Limited )","source":"published"}],"appendages":[{"id":"2-claw-appendages","name":"2 Claw Appendages","source":"published"}],"sensors":[],"integratedSystems":[{"id":"vocabulator","name":"Vocabulator","source":"published"}],"accessories":[],"weapons":[],"sourceText":"Walking Locomotion, Hovering Locomotion ( Limited ), Remote Receiver , 2 Claw Appendages, Vocabulator","sourcePossessions":"Videorecorder , Durasteel Shell ( Droid Armor ; +4 Reflex ) Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 9,600 credits Abilities [ ] Quick Scan: The XLT-014 Labor Droid scans the area in all directions and detects lifeforms or energy signatures within a 6-square radius with a DC 20 Perception check, reducing any Cover and Concealment penalties by half. In addition, with a Use Computer check, the Droid retrieves information from a computer network in half the time. XLT-014 Labor Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Medium 5th-Degree Droid Hit Points: 4 Damage Threshold : 12 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The XLT-014 Labor Droid moves 6 squares ( Walking ) or 6 squares ( Hovering ). Avoid Surprise ( Free Action ) [ ] The XLT-014 Labor Droid makes a Perception check at the start of a battle. If the check is successful, the Droid's master avoids Surprise . Improve Access (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The XLT-014 Labor Droid makes a Use Computer check against a target computer's Will Defense to improve the computer's Attitude toward it. Issue Routine Command (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The XLT-014 Labor Droid issues a routine command to a computer that has a Friendly Attitude toward it. Quick Scan (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] By scanning the area to detect lifeforms, the XLT-014 Labor Droid halves the penalties imposed by Cover and Concealment on its master's attack roll. Base Stats [ ]"},"cl":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"speedText":"6 Squares ( Walking ), 6 Squares ( Hovering ( Limited ))","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Hovering Locomotion ( Limited ), Remote Receiver , 2 Claw Appendages, Vocabulator"}}}
{"_id":"9e8bcb290ea3dd4b","name":"JK-13_Security_Droid","type":"droid","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"degree":"4th-Degree","initiative":13,"senses":"Perception","perception":null,"reflexDefense":24,"flatFooted":22,"fortitudeDefense":29,"willDefense":23,"HP":120,"damageThreshold":44,"speed":8,"baseAttackBonus":null,"grapple":null,"attacks":{"melee":[{"name":"Stun Tentacles","bonus":16,"damage":"3-Square Reach"},{"name":"Stun Tentacles","bonus":14,"damage":"3-Square Reach"},{"name":"Stun Tentacles","bonus":11,"damage":"3-Square Reach"},{"name":"Stun Tentacles","bonus":9,"damage":"3-Square Reach"}],"ranged":[]},"baseStats":{"abilities":{"strength":17,"dexterity":14,"intelligence":10,"wisdom":13,"charisma":11,"constitution":0}},"skills":{"Endurance":11,"Initiative":13,"Use The Force":11},"type":"droid","description":"","costNumeric":50000,"category":"droid","cost":50000,"droidDegreeKey":"4th-degree","droidRole":"security","droidRoleLabel":"Security","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Extra Legs , Climbing Claws , Organic Processor, 10 Probe Appendages, Hardened Systems (x3), Improved Sensor Package , Shield Generator (SR 20)","droidSystems":{"processor":{"id":"organic-processor","name":"Organic Processor","source":"published"},"locomotion":[{"id":"walking-locomotion","name":"Walking Locomotion","source":"published"}],"appendages":[{"id":"10-probe-appendages","name":"10 Probe Appendages","source":"published"}],"sensors":[{"id":"improved-sensor-package","name":"Improved Sensor Package","source":"published"}],"integratedSystems":[{"id":"hardened-systems-x3","name":"Hardened Systems (x3)","source":"published"},{"id":"shield-generator-sr-20","name":"Shield Generator (SR 20)","source":"published"}],"accessories":[{"id":"extra-legs","name":"Extra Legs","source":"published"},{"id":"climbing-claws","name":"Climbing Claws","source":"published"}],"weapons":[{"id":"stun-tentacles","name":"Stun Tentacles","mode":"melee","damage":"3-Square Reach","attackBonus":16,"source":"published-attack"},{"id":"stun-tentacles","name":"Stun Tentacles","mode":"melee","damage":"3-Square Reach","attackBonus":14,"source":"published-attack"},{"id":"stun-tentacles","name":"Stun Tentacles","mode":"melee","damage":"3-Square Reach","attackBonus":11,"source":"published-attack"},{"id":"stun-tentacles","name":"Stun Tentacles","mode":"melee","damage":"3-Square Reach","attackBonus":9,"source":"published-attack"}],"sourceText":"Walking Locomotion, Extra Legs , Climbing Claws , Organic Processor, 10 Probe Appendages, Hardened Systems (x3), Improved Sensor Package , Shield Generator (SR 20)","sourcePossessions":"Stun Tentacles (See Below) Availability: Illegal ; Cost: 50,000 credits Abilities [ ] Killing Rage: If a JK-13 Security Droid reduces an enemy to 0 Hit Points, the Droid flies into a berserk fury, gaining a +2 Rage bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls, but losing the ability to make Use the Force checks, until the end of the encounter. While raging, the JK-13 Droid attacks the nearest target (Friend or foe) until the Droid is destroyed. Stun Tentacles: When a JK-13 Security Droid makes an attack roll with its Stun Tentacles, compare the attack rail to the target's Fortitude Defense as well as its Reflex Defense . If the attack hits both Defenses, the target moves -1 step on the Condition Track ."},"cl":12},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"speedText":"8 Squares ( Walking ), 4 Squares (Climbing); Running Attack","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Extra Legs , Climbing Claws , Organic Processor, 10 Probe Appendages, Hardened Systems (x3), Improved Sensor Package , Shield Generator (SR 20)"}}}
{"_id":"a1772643884db41f","name":"GX1-Series_Battle_Droid","type":"droid","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"degree":"4th-Degree","initiative":18,"senses":"Perception","perception":9,"reflexDefense":24,"flatFooted":21,"fortitudeDefense":20,"willDefense":14,"HP":35,"damageThreshold":20,"speed":6,"baseAttackBonus":null,"grapple":null,"attacks":{"melee":[{"name":"Unarmed","bonus":10,"damage":"1d3+5"}],"ranged":[{"name":"Heavy Blaster Rifle","bonus":11,"damage":"3d10+4"},{"name":"Heavy Blaster Rifle","bonus":9,"damage":"4d10+4"},{"name":"Heavy Blaster Rifle","bonus":11,"damage":"3d10+4"},{"name":"Heavy Blaster Rifle","bonus":9,"damage":"4d10+4"}]},"baseStats":{"abilities":{"strength":16,"dexterity":16,"intelligence":10,"wisdom":8,"charisma":13,"constitution":0}},"skills":{"Initiative":18,"Perception":9},"type":"droid","description":"","costNumeric":23305,"category":"droid","cost":23305,"droidDegreeKey":"4th-degree","droidRole":"battle","droidRoleLabel":"Battle","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Basic Processor , 4 Hand Appendages, 1 Tool Mount, Compartment Space (20 kg), Secondary Battery , Vocabulator","droidSystems":{"processor":{"id":"basic-processor","name":"Basic Processor","source":"published"},"locomotion":[{"id":"walking-locomotion","name":"Walking Locomotion","source":"published"}],"appendages":[{"id":"4-hand-appendages","name":"4 Hand Appendages","source":"published"},{"id":"1-tool-mount","name":"1 Tool Mount","source":"published"}],"sensors":[],"integratedSystems":[{"id":"secondary-battery","name":"Secondary Battery","source":"published"},{"id":"vocabulator","name":"Vocabulator","source":"published"}],"accessories":[{"id":"compartment-space-20-kg","name":"Compartment Space (20 kg)","source":"published"}],"weapons":[{"id":"heavy-blaster-rifle","name":"Heavy Blaster Rifle","mode":"ranged","damage":"3d10+4","attackBonus":11,"source":"published-attack"},{"id":"heavy-blaster-rifle","name":"Heavy Blaster Rifle","mode":"ranged","damage":"4d10+4","attackBonus":9,"source":"published-attack"},{"id":"heavy-blaster-rifle","name":"Heavy Blaster Rifle","mode":"ranged","damage":"3d10+4","attackBonus":11,"source":"published-attack"},{"id":"heavy-blaster-rifle","name":"Heavy Blaster Rifle","mode":"ranged","damage":"4d10+4","attackBonus":9,"source":"published-attack"}],"sourceText":"Walking Locomotion, Basic Processor , 4 Hand Appendages, 1 Tool Mount, Compartment Space (20 kg), Secondary Battery , Vocabulator","sourcePossessions":"Heavy Blaster Rifle , Glow Rod , Durasteel Battle Armor ( Droid Armor ; +8 Reflex ) Availability: Restricted ; Cost: 23,305 credits Abilities [ ] Repositioning Routines: GX1-Series Battle Droids are programmed with sophisticated tactical routines that allow them to regroup and launch a new attack plan when flaws are exposed in their current tactics. Whenever one of the GX1-Series Battle Droid's allies with in 12 squares is reduced to 0 Hit Points, the Battle Droid can move up to half its speed as a Reaction ; this movement does not provoke Attacks of Opportunity . Small Appendages: Two of the GX1-Series Battle Droid's hands are smaller and capable of more fine manipulation than its main hands. A GX1-Series Battle Droid can pick up or retrieve a stowed item as a Free Action once on its turn. GX1-Series Battle Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Medium 4th-Degree Droid Hit Points: 35 Damage Threshold : 20 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The GX1-Series Battle Droid moves 6 squares ( Walking ). Blaster Rifle Attack (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The GX1-Series Battle Droid makes a ranged attack at +11. If successful, the attack deals 3d10+4 points of damage. Rapid Shot (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The GX1-Series Battle Droid makes a ranged attack at +9. If successful, the attack deals 4d10+4 points of damage. Repositioning Routines ( Reaction ) [ ] When one of the GX1-Series Battle Droid's allies within 12 squares is reduced to 0 Hit Points, the Battle Droid can move up to half its speed without provoking Attacks of Opportunity . Retrieve Item ( Free Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The GX1-Series Battle Droid retrieves a stowed item or picks up an item. Base Stats [ ]"},"cl":6},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"speedText":"6 Squares ( Walking ); Repositioning Routines","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Basic Processor , 4 Hand Appendages, 1 Tool Mount, Compartment Space (20 kg), Secondary Battery , Vocabulator"}}}
