oncussion Missiles","mode":"ranged","damage":"(8d10+5","attackBonus":17,"source":"published-attack"},{"id":"proton-torpedoes","name":"Proton Torpedoes","mode":"ranged","damage":"(9d10+5","attackBonus":17,"source":"published-attack"}],"sourceText":"Flying Locomotion, Organic Brain","sourcePossessions":"Heavy Repeating Blaster , Laser Cannon , Ion Cannon , Concussion Missile (8), Proton Torpedo (4), Duranium Battle Armor ( Droid Armor ; +10 Reflex ) Availability: Military ; Cost: 123,000 credits Shadow Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Huge 4th-Degree Droid Hit Points: 120 Damage Threshold : 38 (DR 20) System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The Shadow Droid moves 16 squares ( Flying ). Engage the Enemy (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The Shadow Droid makes a Pilot check with a -5 penalty opposed by the target's Pilot check. If the check is successful, the Droid engages in a Dogfight with the target. Protect and Serve ( Free Action ) [ ] The Shadow Droid spends one of its owner's Force Points to assist an adjacent character. The assisted character can use the Force Point as if he or she had spent it. Ramming Speed (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The Shadow Droid makes a Pilot check with a -10 penalty opposed by the Reflex Defense : of another Starship. If the check is successful, both the target and the Shadow Droid take 4d6+10 points of damage. A failed check deals half damage to both the target and the Shadow Droid. Wingman (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The Shadow Droid assists a character's Pilot check, providing a +2 bonus to the check. Base Stats [ ]"},"cl":9},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"speedText":"16 Squares ( Flying ; Character Scale ), 4 Squares ( Flying ; Starship Scale ); Turn and Burn","droidSystemText":"Flying Locomotion, Organic Brain"}}}
{"_id":"b2e515be636b71d2","name":"MULE_Droid","type":"droid","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"degree":"5th-Degree","initiative":null,"senses":"Perception","perception":12,"reflexDefense":10,"flatFooted":10,"fortitudeDefense":15,"willDefense":11,"HP":9,"damageThreshold":15,"speed":4,"baseAttackBonus":null,"grapple":null,"attacks":{"melee":[{"name":"Unarmed","bonus":6,"damage":"1d4+5"}],"ranged":[]},"baseStats":{"abilities":{"strength":20,"dexterity":10,"intelligence":7,"wisdom":12,"charisma":6,"constitution":0}},"skills":{"Mechanics":9,"Perception":12},"type":"droid","description":"","costNumeric":9000,"category":"droid","cost":9000,"droidDegreeKey":"5th-degree","droidRole":"utility","droidRoleLabel":"Utility","droidSystemText":"Hovering Locomotion, Basic Processor , 1 Claw Appendage, Compartment Space (10 kg), Diagnostics Package Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 9,000 credits Abilities [ ] Self-Diagnostic: The MULE Droid can make a Mechanics check (+11) to determine what repairs it needs. By communicating this information to its master, the Droid grants a +4 bonus to its master's Mechanics check to make the repairs. MULE Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Medium 5th-Degree Droid Hit Points: 9 Damage Threshold : 15 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The MULE Droid moves 4 squares ( Hovering ). Avoid Surprise ( Free Action ) [ ] The MULE Droid makes a Perception check at the start of a battle. If the check is successful, the Droid's master avoids Surprise . Eavesdrop (3 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The MULE Droid can make a Perception check to listen in on conversations and learn information. Notice Targets ( Reaction ) [ ] As a Reaction , with a successful Perception check, the MULE Droid can notice targets that come within its line of sight. Actively searching for hidden enemies is a Standard Action . Self-Diagnostic (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] With a successful Mechanics check (+11), the MULE Droid grants a +4 bonus to its master's Mechanics check on repairs to the Droid. Base Stats [ ] Skills : Mechanics +9 (+11 to Diagnose Problems), Perception +12 Vital Systems: 1 Claw Appendage, Compartment Space (10 kg)","droidSystems":{"processor":{"id":"basic-processor","name":"Basic Processor","source":"published"},"locomotion":[{"id":"hovering-locomotion","name":"Hovering Locomotion","source":"published"},{"id":"the-droid-grants-a-4-bonus-to-its-masters-mechanics-check-to-make-the-repairs-mule-droid-protocol-format-see-also-protocol-format-medium-5th-degree-droid-hit-points-9-damage-threshold-15-system-actions-move-1-swift-action-2-turn-the-mule-droid-moves-4-squares-hovering-avoid-surprise-free-action-the-mule-droid-makes-a-perception-check-at-the-start-of-a-battle-if-the-check-is-successful","name":"the Droid grants a +4 bonus to its master's Mechanics check to make the repairs. MULE Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Medium 5th-Degree Droid Hit Points: 9 Damage Threshold : 15 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action, 2/Turn) [ ] The MULE Droid moves 4 squares ( Hovering ). Avoid Surprise ( Free Action ) [ ] The MULE Droid makes a Perception check at the start of a battle. If the check is successful","source":"published"}],"appendages":[{"id":"1-claw-appendage","name":"1 Claw Appendage","source":"published"},{"id":"perception-12-vital-systems-1-claw-appendage","name":"Perception +12 Vital Systems: 1 Claw Appendage","source":"published"}],"sensors":[],"integratedSystems":[],"accessories":[{"id":"compartment-space-10-kg","name":"Compartment Space (10 kg)","source":"published"},{"id":"diagnostics-package-availability-licensed-cost-9","name":"Diagnostics Package Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 9","source":"published"},{"id":"000-credits-abilities-self-diagnostic-the-mule-droid-can-make-a-mechanics-check-11-to-determine-what-repairs-it-needs-by-communicating-this-information-to-its-master","name":"000 credits Abilities [ ] Self-Diagnostic: The MULE Droid can make a Mechanics 