{"_id":"c23355ec28d87e31","name":"HKB-3_Hunter-Killer_Droid","type":"droid","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"degree":"4th-Degree","initiative":null,"senses":"Perception","perception":11,"reflexDefense":18,"flatFooted":17,"fortitudeDefense":19,"willDefense":15,"HP":32,"damageThreshold":19,"speed":6,"baseAttackBonus":null,"grapple":null,"attacks":{"melee":[{"name":"Unarmed","bonus":8,"damage":"1d3+4"}],"ranged":[{"name":"Blaster Rifle","bonus":8,"damage":"3d8+4"},{"name":"Blaster Rifle","bonus":6,"damage":"4d8+4"},{"name":"Blaster Rifle","bonus":8,"damage":"3d8+4"},{"name":"Blaster Rifle","bonus":6,"damage":"4d8+4"}]},"baseStats":{"abilities":{"strength":14,"dexterity":13,"intelligence":12,"wisdom":10,"charisma":8,"constitution":0}},"skills":{"Perception":11,"Stealth":10,"Survival":9},"type":"droid","description":"","costNumeric":19130,"category":"droid","cost":19130,"droidDegreeKey":"4th-degree","droidRole":"assassin","droidRoleLabel":"Assassin","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Remote Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, Improved Sensor Package , Internal Comlink (Encrypted), Locked Access , Vocabulator","droidSystems":{"processor":{"id":"remote-processor","name":"Remote Processor","source":"published"},"locomotion":[{"id":"walking-locomotion","name":"Walking Locomotion","source":"published"}],"appendages":[{"id":"2-hand-appendages","name":"2 Hand Appendages","source":"published"}],"sensors":[{"id":"improved-sensor-package","name":"Improved Sensor Package","source":"published"}],"integratedSystems":[{"id":"internal-comlink-encrypted","name":"Internal Comlink (Encrypted)","source":"published"},{"id":"locked-access","name":"Locked Access","source":"published"},{"id":"vocabulator","name":"Vocabulator","source":"published"}],"accessories":[],"weapons":[{"id":"blaster-rifle","name":"Blaster Rifle","mode":"ranged","damage":"3d8+4","attackBonus":8,"source":"published-attack"},{"id":"blaster-rifle","name":"Blaster Rifle","mode":"ranged","damage":"4d8+4","attackBonus":6,"source":"published-attack"},{"id":"blaster-rifle","name":"Blaster Rifle","mode":"ranged","damage":"3d8+4","attackBonus":8,"source":"published-attack"},{"id":"blaster-rifle","name":"Blaster Rifle","mode":"ranged","damage":"4d8+4","attackBonus":6,"source":"published-attack"}],"sourceText":"Walking Locomotion, Remote Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, Improved Sensor Package , Internal Comlink (Encrypted), Locked Access , Vocabulator","sourcePossessions":"Blaster Rifle , Quadanium Plating ( Droid Armor ; +5 Reflex ) Availability: Military ; Cost: 19,130 credits Abilities [ ] Coordinated Tracking: HKB-3 Droids share sensor and observational data when tracking a target. When up to four HKB-3 Droids are Tracking the same target and each Droid is within 30 squares of at least one other Droid in the group, each Droid makes a Survival check to Track the target, and all Droids use the highest result. The Droids also automatically Aid Another on the check. Hunting Sensor: HKB-3 Droids carry specialized sensors for hunting targets that negate all Cover and Concealment penalties to Perception checks, including Total Cover and Total Concealment . The sensors do not negate Cover and Concealment penalties to attacks. Simultaneous Fire: When the HKB-3 Droid uses the Aid Another Action to aid another HKB-3 Droid's attack roll, that Droid's attack, if it hits, deals +1 die of damage for every 5 points by which it exceeded the target's Reflex Defense . Multiple HKB-3 Droids using the Aid Another Action stack their attack bonuses, but this bonus to damage is only applied once. HKB-3 Hunter-Killer Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Medium 4th-Degree Droid Hit Points: 32 Damage Threshold : 19 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The HKB-3 Hunter-Killer Droid moves 6 squares ( Walking ). Blaster Rifle Attack (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The HKB-3 Hunter-Killer Droid makes a ranged attack at +8. If successful, the attack deals 3d8+4 points of damage. Coordinated Tracking (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The HKB-3 Hunter-Killer Droid makes a Survival check to Track a target. When up to four HKB-3 Droids are Tracking the same target and each Droid is within 30 squares of at least one other Droid in the group, each Droid makes a Survival check to Track the target, and all Droids use the highest result. The Droids also automatically Aid Another on the check. Simultaneous Fire (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The HKB-3 Hunter-Killer Droid uses the Aid Another Action to aid another HKB-3 Droid's attack roll, granting the allied Droid +1 die of damage for every 5 points by which the Droid's attack roll exceeds its target's Reflex Defense . Multiple HKB-3 Droids using Simultaneous Fire stack their attack bonuses, but this bonus to damage is only applied once. Base Stats [ ]"},"cl":6},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"speedText":"6 Squares ( Walking ); Expert Tracker","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Remote Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, Improved Sensor Package , Internal Comlink (Encrypted), Locked Access , Vocabulator"}}}
{"_id":"c31efa8505462180","name":"MK-Series_Maintenance_Droid","type":"droid","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"degree":"2nd-Degree","initiative":7,"senses":"Perception","perception":5,"reflexDefense":14,"flatFooted":12,"fortitudeDefense":12,"willDefense":11,"HP":24,"damageThreshold":12,"speed":6,"baseAttackBonus":null,"grapple":null,"attacks":{"melee":[{"name":"Unarmed","bonus":-1,"damage":"1d4-1"}],"ranged":[]},"baseStats":{"abilities":{"strength":9,"dexterity":14,"intelligence":15,"wisdom":10,"charisma":13,"constitution":0}},"skills":{"Endurance":5,"Initiative":7,"Mechanics":12,"Perception":5,"Pilot":7,"Use Computer":12},"type":"droid","description":"","costNumeric":11080,"category":"droid","cost":11080,"droidDegreeKey":"2nd-degree","droidRole":"repair","droidRoleLabel":"Repair","cl":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"speedText":"6 Squares ( Tracked )"}}}
{"_id":"c9506459353f4e1b","name":"RX-Series_Pilot_Droid","type":"droid","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"degree":"2nd-Degree","initiative":null,"senses":"Perception","perception":1,"reflexDefense":12,"flatFooted":10,"fortitudeDefense":10,"willDefense":9,"HP":10,"damageThreshold":10,"speed":6,"baseAttackBonus":null,"grapple":null,"attacks":{"melee":[{"name":"Unarmed","bonus":3,"damage":"1d4"}],"ranged":[]},"baseStats":{"abilities":{"strength":10,"dexterity":15,"intelligence":13,"wisdom":8,"charisma":12,"constitution":0}},"skills":{"Mechanics":8,"Perception":1,"Pilot":14,"Use Computer":8},"type":"droid","description":"","costNumeric":9855,"category":"droid","cost":9855,"droidDegreeKey":"2nd-degree","droidRole":"pilot","droidRoleLabel":"Pilot","droidSystemText":"Hovering Locomotion, Heuristic Processor , 3 Claw Appendages, Vocabulator Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 9,855 credits Abilities [ ] Hot-Shot Pilot: The RX-Series Pilot Droid can reroll its Pilot check to Avoid Collision and can take the better of the two results. In addition, once per encounter as a Reaction , the Droid can avoid an attack from a missile or a torpedo by making a Pilot check against the attack roll. If the result of the Pilot check equals or exceeds the attack roll, the missile or torpedo is dodged for that round of combat. RX-Series Pilot Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Medium 2nd-Degree Droid Hit Points: 10 Damage Threshold : 10 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid moves 6 squares ( Hovering ). Engage the Enemy (1 Free Action ) [ ] At the start of a battle, the RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a Pilot check instead of an Initiative check. Hot-Shot Pilot ( Reaction , 1/Encounter) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a Pilot check to Avoid Collision or an incoming missile or torpedo. Increase Vehicle Speed (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a DC 20 Pilot check. If the check is successful, the Vehicle increases its speed by 1 square plus 1 square for every 5 points by which the check result exceeds the DC. Recharge Shields (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a DC 20 Mechanics check. If the check is successful, the Vehicle regains 5 points of its Shield Rating , up to its normal maximum. Regulate Power (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a DC 20 Mechanics check. If the check is successful, the Vehicle moves +1 step along the Condition Track . Base Stats [ ] Skills : Knowledge (Galactic Lore) +8, Mechanics +8, Pilot +14, Use Computer +8 Vital Systems: 3 Claw Appendages, Vocabulator","droidSystems":{"processor":{"id":"heuristic-processor","name":"Heuristic Processor","source":"published"},"locomotion":[{"id":"hovering-locomotion","name":"Hovering Locomotion","source":"published"},{"id":"the-missile-or-torpedo-is-dodged-for-that-round-of-combat-rx-series-pilot-droid-protocol-format-see-also-protocol-format-medium-2nd-degree-droid-hit-points-10-damage-threshold-10-system-actions-move-1-swift-action-2-turn-the-rx-series-pilot-droid-moves-6-squares-hovering-engage-the-enemy-1-free-action-at-the-start-of-a-battle","name":"the missile or torpedo is dodged for that round of combat. RX-Series Pilot Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Medium 2nd-Degree Droid Hit Points: 10 Damage Threshold : 10 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action, 2/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid moves 6 squares ( Hovering ). Engage the Enemy (1 Free Action ) [ ] At the start of a battle","source":"published"}],"appendages":[{"id":"3-claw-appendages","name":"3 Claw Appendages","source":"published"},{"id":"use-computer-8-vital-systems-3-claw-appendages","name":"Use Computer +8 Vital Systems: 3 Claw Appendages","source":"published"}],"sensors":[],"integratedSystems":[{"id":"vocabulator-availability-licensed-cost-9","name":"Vocabulator Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 9","source":"published"},{"id":"the-vehicle-increases-its-speed-by-1-square-plus-1-square-for-every-5-points-by-which-the-check-result-exceeds-the-dc-recharge-shields-2-swift-actions-1-turn-the-rx-series-pilot-droid-makes-a-dc-20-mechanics-check-if-the-check-is-successful","name":"the Vehicle increases its speed by 1 square plus 1 square for every 5 points by which the check result exceeds the DC. Recharge Shields (2 Swift Actions, 1/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a DC 20 Mechanics check. If the check is successful","source":"published"},{"id":"the-vehicle-regains-5-points-of-its-shield-rating","name":"the Vehicle regains 5 points of its Shield Rating","source":"published"},{"id":"vocabulator","name":"Vocabulator","source":"published"}],"accessories":[{"id":"855-credits-abilities-hot-shot-pilot-the-rx-series-pilot-droid-can-reroll-its-pilot-check-to-avoid-collision-and-can-take-the-better-of-the-two-results-in-addition","name":"855 credits Abilities [ ] Hot-Shot Pilot: The RX-Series Pilot Droid can reroll its Pilot check to Avoid Collision and can take the better of the two results. In addition","source":"published"},{"id":"once-per-encounter-as-a-reaction","name":"once per encounter as a Reaction","source":"published"},{"id":"the-droid-can-avoid-an-attack-from-a-missile-or-a-torpedo-by-making-a-pilot-check-against-the-attack-roll-if-the-result-of-the-pilot-check-equals-or-exceeds-the-attack-roll","name":"the Droid can avoid an attack from a missile or a torpedo by making a Pilot check against the attack roll. If the result of the Pilot check equals or exceeds the attack roll","source":"published"},{"id":"the-rx-series-pilot-droid-makes-a-pilot-check-instead-of-an-initiative-check-hot-shot-pilot-reaction-1-encounter-the-rx-series-pilot-droid-makes-a-pilot-check-to-avoid-collision-or-an-incoming-missile-or-torpedo-increase-vehicle-speed-1-swift-action-1-turn-the-rx-series-pilot-droid-makes-a-dc-20-pilot-check-if-the-check-is-successful","name":"the RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a Pilot check instead of an Initiative check. Hot-Shot Pilot ( Reaction, 1/Encounter) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a Pilot check to Avoid Collision or an incoming missile or torpedo. Increase Vehicle Speed (1 Swift Action, 1/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a DC 20 Pilot check. If the check is successful","source":"published"},{"id":"up-to-its-normal-maximum-regulate-power-2-swift-actions-1-turn-the-rx-series-pilot-droid-makes-a-dc-20-mechanics-check-if-the-check-is-successful","name":"up to its normal maximum. Regulate Power (2 Swift Actions, 1/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a DC 20 Mechanics check. If the check is successful","source":"published"},{"id":"the-vehicle-moves-1-step-along-the-condition-track-base-stats-skills-knowledge-galactic-lore-8","name":"the Vehicle moves +1 step along the Condition Track . Base Stats [ ] Skills : Knowledge (Galactic Lore) +8","source":"published"},{"id":"mechanics-8","name":"Mechanics +8","source":"published"},{"id":"pilot-14","name":"Pilot +14","source":"published"}],"weapons":[],"sourceText":"Hovering Locomotion, Heuristic Processor , 3 Claw Appendages, Vocabulator Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 9,855 credits Abilities [ ] Hot-Shot Pilot: The RX-Series Pilot Droid can reroll its Pilot check to Avoid Collision and can take the better of the two results. In addition, once per encounter as a Reaction , the Droid can avoid an attack from a missile or a torpedo by making a Pilot check against the attack roll. If the result of the Pilot check equals or exceeds the attack roll, the missile or torpedo is dodged for that round of combat. RX-Series Pilot Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Medium 2nd-Degree Droid Hit Points: 10 Damage Threshold : 10 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid moves 6 squares ( Hovering ). Engage the Enemy (1 Free Action ) [ ] At the start of a battle, the RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a Pilot check instead of an Initiative check. Hot-Shot Pilot ( Reaction , 1/Encounter) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a Pilot check to Avoid Collision or an incoming missile or torpedo. Increase Vehicle Speed (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a DC 20 Pilot check. If the check is successful, the Vehicle increases its speed by 1 square plus 1 square for every 5 points by which the check result exceeds the DC. Recharge Shields (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a DC 20 Mechanics check. If the check is successful, the Vehicle regains 5 points of its Shield Rating , up to its normal maximum. Regulate Power (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a DC 20 Mechanics check. If the check is successful, the Vehicle moves +1 step along the Condition Track . Base Stats [ ] Skills : Knowledge (Galactic Lore) +8, Mechanics +8, Pilot +14, Use Computer +8 Vital Systems: 3 Claw Appendages, Vocabulator"},"cl":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"speedText":"6 Squares ( Hovering )","droidSystemText":"Hovering Locomotion, Heuristic Processor , 3 Claw Appendages, Vocabulator Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 9,855 credits Abilities [ ] Hot-Shot Pilot: The RX-Series Pilot Droid can reroll its Pilot check to Avoid Collision and can take the better of the two results. In addition, once per encounter as a Reaction , the Droid can avoid an attack from a missile or a torpedo by making a Pilot check against the attack roll. If the result of the Pilot check equals or exceeds the attack roll, the missile or torpedo is dodged for that round of combat. RX-Series Pilot Droid Protocol Format [ ] See also: Protocol Format Medium 2nd-Degree Droid Hit Points: 10 Damage Threshold : 10 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid moves 6 squares ( Hovering ). Engage the Enemy (1 Free Action ) [ ] At the start of a battle, the RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a Pilot check instead of an Initiative check. Hot-Shot Pilot ( Reaction , 1/Encounter) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a Pilot check to Avoid Collision or an incoming missile or torpedo. Increase Vehicle Speed (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a DC 20 Pilot check. If the check is successful, the Vehicle increases its speed by 1 square plus 1 square for every 5 points by which the check result exceeds the DC. Recharge Shields (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a DC 20 Mechanics check. If the check is successful, the Vehicle regains 5 points of its Shield Rating , up to its normal maximum. Regulate Power (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The RX-Series Pilot Droid makes a DC 20 Mechanics check. If the check is successful, the Vehicle moves +1 step along the Condition Track . Base Stats [ ] Skills : Knowledge (Galactic Lore) +8, Mechanics +8, Pilot +14, Use Computer +8 Vital Systems: 3 Claw Appendages, Vocabulator"}}}
