{"_id":"f33f22a717031d35","name":"2-1B_Medical_Droid","type":"droid","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"degree":"1st-Degree","initiative":null,"senses":"Perception","perception":5,"reflexDefense":10,"flatFooted":10,"fortitudeDefense":9,"willDefense":12,"HP":5,"damageThreshold":9,"speed":6,"baseAttackBonus":null,"grapple":null,"attacks":{"melee":[{"name":"Unarmed","bonus":0,"damage":"1d3-1"}],"ranged":[]},"baseStats":{"abilities":{"strength":8,"dexterity":11,"intelligence":14,"wisdom":15,"charisma":9,"constitution":0}},"skills":{"Perception":5,"Treat Injury":13,"Use Computer":8},"type":"droid","description":"","costNumeric":7150,"category":"droid","cost":7150,"droidDegreeKey":"1st-degree","droidRole":"medical","droidRoleLabel":"Medical","droidSystemText":"Walking Locomotion, Heuristic Processor , 2 Hand Appendages, Improved Sensor Package , Vocabulator Availability: Licensed ; Cost: 7,150 credits 2-1B Medical Droid Protocol Format [ ] Reference Book: Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids See also: Protocol Format Medium 1st-Degree Droid Hit Points: 5 Damage Threshold : 9 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action , 2/Turn) [ ] The 2-1B Medical Droid moves 6 squares ( Walking ). Diagnosis (1 Free Action ) [ ] The 2-1B Medical Droid makes a Knowledge (Life Sciences) check to determine a source of disease or injury and communicates this diagnosis to its owner. First Aid (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The 2-1B Medical Droid makes a DC 15 Treat Injury check on a target in an adjacent square. If the check is successful, the target regains a number of Hit Points equal to its Character Level +1 for every point by which the check was successful. A character can be treated with First Aid in this manner only once per day. Medical Assistance (1 Swift Action , 1/Turn) [ ] The 2-1B Medical Droid assists a character's Treat Injury check, providing a +2 bonus to the check. Revivify (2 Swift Actions , 1/Turn) [ ] The 2-1B Medical Droid makes a DC 20 Treat Injury check on a target currently at 0 Hit Points in an adjacent square. If the check is successful, the target is Unconscious instead of Dead . Base Stats [ ] Skills : Knowledge (Life Sciences) +13, Treat Injury +13, Use Computer +8 Vital Systems: 2 Hand Appendages, Vocabulator","droidSystems":{"processor":{"id":"heuristic-processor","name":"Heuristic Processor","source":"published"},"locomotion":[{"id":"walking-locomotion","name":"Walking Locomotion","source":"published"},{"id":"150-credits-2-1b-medical-droid-protocol-format-reference-book-star-wars-saga-edition-scavengers-guide-to-droids-see-also-protocol-format-medium-1st-degree-droid-hit-points-5-damage-threshold-9-system-actions-move-1-swift-action-2-turn-the-2-1b-medical-droid-moves-6-squares-walking-diagnosis-1-free-action-the-2-1b-medical-droid-makes-a-knowledge-life-sciences-check-to-determine-a-source-of-disease-or-injury-and-communicates-this-diagnosis-to-its-owner-first-aid-2-swift-actions-1-turn-the-2-1b-medical-droid-makes-a-dc-15-treat-injury-check-on-a-target-in-an-adjacent-square-if-the-check-is-successful","name":"150 credits 2-1B Medical Droid Protocol Format [ ] Reference Book: Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids See also: Protocol Format Medium 1st-Degree Droid Hit Points: 5 Damage Threshold : 9 System Actions [ ] Move (1 Swift Action, 2/Turn) [ ] The 2-1B Medical Droid moves 6 squares ( Walking ). Diagnosis (1 Free Action ) [ ] The 2-1B Medical Droid makes a Knowledge (Life Sciences) check to determine a source of disease or injury and communicates this diagnosis to its owner. First Aid (2 Swift Actions, 1/Turn) [ ] The 2-1B Medical Droid makes a DC 15 Treat Injury check on a target in an adjacent square. If the check is successful","source":"published"}],"appendages":[{"id":"2-hand-appendages","name":"2 Hand Appendages","source":"published"},{"id":"use-computer-8-vital-systems-2-hand-appendages","name":"Use Computer +8 Vital Systems: 2 Hand Appendages","source":"published"}],"sensors"